Basic Scanning Commands

Scan a Single Target: This command scans a single target specified by its IP address.

bash
Copy code
nmap 192.168.0.1
Scan Multiple Targets: This command scans multiple targets specified by their respective IP addresses.

bash
Copy code
nmap 192.168.0.1 192.168.0.2
Scan a Range of Hosts: This command scans a range of hosts specified by the starting and ending IP addresses.

bash
Copy code
nmap 192.168.0.1-10
Scan an Entire Subnet: This command scans an entire subnet by specifying the base IP address followed by the subnet mask in CIDR notation.

bash
Copy code
nmap 192.168.0.1/24
Scan Random Hosts: This command scans a specified number of randomly chosen hosts.

bash
Copy code
nmap -iR 0
Excluding Targets from a Scan: This command excludes specified targets from the scan.

bash
Copy code
nmap 192.168.0.1/24 --exclude 192.168.0.100,192.168.0.200
Excluding Targets Using a List: This command excludes targets listed in a file from the scan.

bash
Copy code
nmap 192.168.0.1/24 --excludefile notargets.txt
Perform an Aggressive Scan (-A): This command performs an aggressive scan, enabling OS detection, version detection, script scanning, and traceroute.

bash
Copy code
nmap -A 192.168.0.1
Scan an IPv6 Target (-6): This command scans an IPv6 target specified by its address.

bash
Copy code
nmap -6 1aff:3c21:47b1:0000:0000:0000:0000:2afe
